EMERGING ISSUES IN OUR SOCIETY IN THE ICT SECTOR.

From the early man era until our current generation, technology and our ICT industry has really evolved. This has definitely influenced our society and may have solved or brought up issues in these societies. 

ICT has greatly influenced our generation and now even during the covid pandemic era. It has created challenges, solutions and even opportunities for us all. The following are emerging issues in our societies based on the growth of ICT:

Cyber security-

Technology has spread through knowledge and can be manipulated in many ways, including harmful ways. Governments, households and individuals are vulnerable to breach in cyber space. Cyber risk is one of the top challenges emerging due to technological advancements since hack attacks and other security breaches could cost us our global economy. A study conducted by international data group showed that in Kenya alone, cybercrime costs our economy about 36 million dollars. Some main methods used by cyber criminals in Kenya include; spyware, password theft and ATM piracy.



Geographical blocking-

This is widely used in the EU and is basically restricting access to internet content based on your geo-location at that time. This limits cross-border portability which is where a lawful subscriber cannot access what they need when in a location that is not allowed access to. It also limits cross-border trade which is restricted access that hinders trade among different parties of different locations. This hinders opportunities for trade, economic growth and relations among states.



Internet of things-

This is an interconnection of many different networks. In Africa, there is a slow adoption of IoT compared to other continents. This would have revolutionized many vital sectors including health and agriculture. Inadequate skills, finances and resources or knowledge has made it very hard for Africa to hop on this. It would have solved many problems even for the consumer, e.g., poor service or product quality.



Funding-

In Africa, there is a significant challenge in adequately planning and financing the use of ICT in development programs. With little donor funding and pressure to reduce administrative expenses, it becomes difficult for INGOs to plan and finance these programs.

and brought about the rise in new trends in the sector. These trends have really assisted during the pandemic and has proven possibilities are endless. These trends include;



Cloud computing-

This is the definite online data storage facility for an organization or institution. This has been implemented by many institutions to protect, preserve and care for their digital information, resources and data. It helps in improving work efficiency and defining your digital space.



Mobile apps-

Mobile applications are been created daily to enable easy access to services, information, trading etc. it has been implemented in almost all sectors of the economy as it is fast and quick to retrieve or store information and communicate easily.



Big data analytics-

This is a trend that aids in an organizations planning and strategy. It simply allows them to process their data in a better manner and enables them to better understand their improvement areas.



Artificial intelligence-

Industries are using this trend to grow and manage their resources and implement their work. It is one of the latest trends with a huge possibility to grow.



Virtual reality-

VR games have started been implemented in other industries to grow itself since it creates the very epitome of digital experience enabling them to relate better with their customers.



Block chain data-

Block chain technology has given rise to crypto currency which has enabled the massive growth of an economy. It has the capability to grow the economy twice as much and is being implemented daily.



Growth of IoT networks-

The internet of things has enabled the connection of an individuals every aspect of life to their own homes. This has spearheaded in trying to still build the economy even during a pandemic by virtually carrying out our businesses.



Quantum computing applications-

This is conducting complex equations and processes to perform several complex tasks in absolute ease. This has massively grown as industries have incorporated it.
